知っている人は知っている。知らない人も今後知ることになるだろう。そんなマーベルの新ヒーロー？がまた一人誕生しました…その名も「デッドプール」！！
新ヒーローと言いましたが、アメコミに初登場したのは1991年。実写版映画では2009年「ウルヴァリン X-MEN ZERO」で悪役として登場。それが2016年、主人公として映画化されることになりました！ブラックユーモアを交えながら、これまでのヒーロー像をぶち壊して突き進んでいくデップー。この男の進む道は正義なのか？悪なのか？…本人もしったこっちゃねぇ～(笑)
マーベルイヤーに入ってから、「アベンジャーズ：エイジ・オブ・ウルトロン」「アントマン」「バットマンVSスーパーマン」続々と公開されるアメコミヒーロー達。その中でも異彩を放つデットプールは、R指定ながら初週週末興行成績は、スターウォーズ・アバターを抜き、FOX映画史上最高記録を達成。日本上陸は2016年6月公開予定。楽しみですね～(^0^*
ポスターは、アメコミ版デットプールです。COOLにいこうぜベイビー！

アメリカ合衆国ミズーリ州に生まれたエミネム。貧しい幼少時代を経て14歳ごろからヒップホップMCとして頭角を現し、その後過激な歌詞で話題を呼んだファーストアルバムは600万枚というセールスを記録。一躍スターダムにのし上がります。
思いに耽るエミネムの胸に去来するものは…。実はこの写真、後に写っているのは、エミネムが幼少時代を過ごしたデトロイト・ドレスデンstの19946番地にある実家。「The Marshall Mathers LP」のジャケットにもなりましたね。モノクロ写真が素敵です！

マーベルイヤーに入ってから、「アベンジャーズ：エイジ・オブ・ウルトロン」「アントマン」「バットマンVSスーパーマン」続々と公開されるアメコミヒーロー達。その中でも異彩を放つデットプールは、R指定ながら初週週末興行成績は、スターウォーズ・アバターを抜き、FOX映画史上最高記録を達成。日本上陸は2016年6月公開予定。楽しみですね～(^0^*
ポスターは、アメコミ版デットプールです。COOLにいこうぜベイビー！

In Symphony is a collection of his best-known tracks - plus a couple of surprises - re-recorded over five days at Abbey Road Studio. With over 30 chart-topping hits and sales of 360 million records for himself as well as artists such as Leo Sayer, Diana Ross, The Hollies, Whitney Houston and Starship, it would be tempting for Albert to hang up the guitar and take it easy. But he's still writing and gigging, and after one especially energetic televised live solo show in Berlin last year, label execs wanted to hear more from the London-born, Gibraltar-raised performer. ""This is a record that's not supposed to happen,"" he laughs, ""The BMG people came to see me after the show and said, 'We want to do something. ' I said 'Well, I don't, unless I do my hits symphonically... '"" こちらの商品は輸入盤のため、稀にジャケットに多少のスレや角にシワがある場合がございます。

商品紹介
南米コロンビア産の異能ポップ・バンド、メリディアン・ブラザーズの日本デビュー・アルバム。
多種多様なラテン～カリビアンのリズムの上をキーボードやシンセがピロピロと狂い飛ぶ様は、一度聴けば病みつきに。
ファニーだけど不気味、独創的で不思議なローファイ・ラテン+電子音楽ワールド。

Original cast recording. 2016 release that contains songs taken from the current National Theatre production wonder. Land by Rufus Norris, Moira Buffini and Damon Albarn. #wonder. Land debuted at Manchester International Festival in June last year and transferred to the National Theatre's Olivier last November, where it has delighted the public and seen the National double it's number of new visitors. The musical, inspired by Lewis Carroll's Alice In Wonderland, is a coming-of-age adventure that explores the blurred boundaries between our online and offline lives and follows school-girl Aly as she struggles with the pressures of being a teenager. She discovers wonder. Land - a mysterious online world where she hopes to create a whole new life. The web becomes her looking-glass but soon she starts to question if she sees who she really is. こちらの商品は輸入盤のため、稀にジャケットに多少のスレや角にシワがある場合がございます。

Much has been written about West Side Story, which began as a transmogrification of Romeo and Juliet as a feud between the Jews and Gentiles living on the East side in modern-day New York, only to morph into a confrontation between two street gangs, one American the other Puerto Rican, on the upper West side of the city. Initially, Leonard Bernstein, it's composer, was to have written both music and lyrics, but Stephen Sondheim was eventually brought in to handle the latter. With Arthur Laurents contributing the book, and Jerome Robbins devising the staging, the show opened to great acclaim on September 26, 1957 at the Winter Garden, where it played 732 performances, and was subsequently revived several times on Broadway and around the country. But it was the film version, made three years later with Natalie Wood as Maria, that ensured it's popularity worldwide. Though there are many recorded versions of the percussive score available, the original cast album, with it's fresh, spontaneous performances, remains the standard by which all others are measured.こちらの商品は輸入盤のため、稀にジャケットに多少のスレや角にシワがある場合がございます。

South Pacific opened on April 7, 1949 at the Majestic Theatre, and enjoyed one of the longest runs on Broadway up to that time (1, 925 performances)
column2:
it deservedly won the Pulitzer Prize, along with a plethora of Tony Awards. This is the first vinyl reissue of this album cut from the original mono tapes by Ryan K. Smith at Sterling Sound and pressed and plated at RTI. South Pacific was composed by Richard Rodgers, with lyrics by Oscar Hammerstein II and book by Hammerstein and Joshua Logan. The plot of the musical is based on James A. Michener's Pulitzer Prize-winning 1947 book Tales of the South Pacific and combines elements of several of those stories. Rodgers and Hammerstein believed they could write a musical based on Michener's work that would be financially successful and, at the same time, would send a strong progressive message on racism. こちらの商品は輸入盤のため、稀にジャケットに多少のスレや角にシワがある場合がございます。

23-5274,http://tshop.r10s.jp/americanpie/cabinet/lp8/anogas00026vinyl.jpg?fitin=700:700,3592.0000,,CD・DVD・楽器 > CD > サウンドトラック > 洋画 > その他,Original Broadway Cast / Gypsy (180gram Vinyl)【輸入盤LPﾚｺｰﾄﾞ】【LP2017/4/21発売】(ﾐｭｰｼﾞｶﾙ),【ただ今クーポン発行中です】,"Limited 180gm vinyl LP pressing housed in a Stoughton old style ""tip-on"" jacket. This was the first stereo recording of Ethel Merman, produced by legendary Broadway cast recording producer Goddard Lieberson and recorded at Columbia 30th Street Studios. This is the first vinyl reissue of this album cut from the original stereo master tapes by Ryan K. Smith at Sterling Sound and pressed and plated at RTI. Gypsy is a 1959 musical with music by Jule Styne, lyrics by Stephen Sondheim, and a book by Arthur Laurents. Gypsy is loosely based on the 1957 memoirs of Gypsy Rose Lee, the famous striptease artist, and focuses on her mother, Rose, whose name has become synonymous with ""the ultimate show business mother."" It follows the dreams and efforts of Rose to raise two daughters to perform onstage and casts an affectionate eye on the hardships of show business life. Gypsy has been referred to as the greatest American musical by numerous critics and writers, among them Ben Brantley (""what may be the greatest of all American musicals..."") and Frank Rich. Rich wrote that ""Gypsy is nothing if not Broadway's own brassy, unlikely answer to 'King Lear.'"" Theater critic Clive Barnes wrote that ""'Gypsy' is one of the best of musicals..."" and described the character of Rose as ""one of the few truly complex characters in the American musical..."" こちらの商品は輸入盤のため、稀にジャケットに多少のスレや角にシワがある場合がございます。
